17/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- A freelance US journalist has been arrested in Istanbul for alleged ties to the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK), news agencies reported on Monday (August 16th). 
Jake Hess, 25, a freelance writer from New Hampshire, was reporting on the mistreatment of Kurds and was working as a translator for a human rights organisation in Diyarbakir, his lawyer said. 
He is currently at a foreigners' detention facility awaiting deportation. 
(Washington Post, CNN, UPI - 16/08/10)
